      <data key="d3">paper-01:chunk_0008</data>
      <data key="d4">method</data>
      <data key="d5">Rather than serving as a taxonomy of methods, the REO framework identifies three fundamental components of discovery: representation of candidate equations, evaluation of their validity, and optimization of the search process.</data>
